==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Digenesis
<hw>Di*gen"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>genesis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The
faculty of multiplying in two ways; -- by ova fecundated by spermatic
fluid, and asexually, as by buds. See
<er>Parthenogenesis</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Digenous</ent>⟦br⟧
